            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_213gc' title='Col. 213GC &mdash; HL Deb 04 May 2004 vol 660 c213GC' name='column_213gc' href='#column_213gc' rel='bookmark'>213GC</a>
            down outside the House by cyclists not obeying the red lights. Of course, currently, I do not think that anyone can stop a cyclist except a policeman because he or she is on a moving vehicle. I am sure that my noble friend will correct me if I am wrong. Cyclists riding on pavements are also a problem.</p><p>
